# No Cursor / AI attribution in git artifacts

When creating git commits, pull requests, or any code/comment in this
repository, **never** add attribution to Cursor, the AI agent, or any
tool. Specifically:

- Do **not** append `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
  (or any variation) to commit messages.
- Do **not** append `Made-with: Cursor`, `Generated-by: …`,
  `Assisted-by: …`, or similar trailers.
- Do **not** add "🤖 Generated with [Claude Code]…", "Co-Authored-By:
  Claude …", or any other AI-tool attribution to commit messages or PR
  bodies.
- Do **not** add comments like `// AI-generated` / `// generated by
  Cursor` to source files.

Commits should appear as if written by the human author alone. The
author identity comes from `git config user.name` / `user.email`;
nothing else should be added to the commit trailer block.

This rule exists because the trailer surfaces as a `cursoragent`
co-author on GitHub, which the project owner explicitly does not want.
